 BC-13 AD)<br />\r\n			Transfert à la gare. Train pour Tachkent à 18.00. Arrivée à 20.10. Transfert et hébergement à l’hôtel.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dîner libre</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\"><strong>JOUR 6</strong></td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Tachkent</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Petit déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Transfert à l\'aéroport selon l\'horaire du vol. Envol.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Fin de nos services ...</em></strong><br />\r\n			&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '2', 'App\Models\Tour');
INSERT INTO translations (locale, column_name, value, translatable_id, translatable_type) VALUES ('it', 'route_lines', '<table class=\"table tour-table-rounded\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th style=\"width:8%;\">Giorni</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:14%;\">Tappe</th>\r\n			<th>Soggetti dell’itinerario</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 1</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p class=\"justifyfull\">Arrivo a Tashkent. Trasferimento e sistemazione in alberghi.<br />\r\n			Tempo libero.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p class=\"justifyfull\"><strong>Pranzo libero.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Tashkent: </em></strong>Visita alla metropolitana di Tashkent, Chiesa cattolica polacca, Kirsch tedesco. Kukeldash Madrassah, Mausoleo di Kaffal Shashi, Barak Khan Madrassah, Moschea in Khasty Imam Street, Visita a Chor-Su – mercato orientale (bazar dell\'artigianato)<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 2</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">Tashkent - Bukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td valign=\"top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			&nbsp;Trasferimento alla stazione ferroviaria, treno per Bukhara alle 07.30. Arrivo alle 11:20 e sistemazione in albergo.<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero.</strong><br />\r\n			Tempo libero.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 3</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">Bukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p class=\"justifyfull\"><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Bukhara: </em></strong> Poi-Kalyan Ensemble che include Minareto (12c) Moschea (15c), Madrassah Miri-Arab funzionante (16c), Emir-Alim-Khan Madrassah (14c), Taqi (cupole commerciali), Kukeldash Madrassah (16c) , Nadir Divanbegi (17c), Moschea Magok-i-Attari (16c), Lyab-i-Hauz (17c).<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero. </strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Bukhara: </em></strong>: Visita al Registan, alla Fortezza dell\'Arca (16 sec) e al complesso Bolo-Hauz (18 sec). Ulug Beg (15c), Abdul Aziz (17c) Mausoleo di Ismael Samani (9-10c)-volta della dinastia dei sovrani di Bukhara, Mausolei di Chashma-Ayub (14c)<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 4</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">Bukhara - Samarcanda</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			Tempo libero.<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero.</strong><br />\r\n			Trasferimento alla stazione ferroviaria, treno per Samarcanda alle 15.50, arrivo alle 17.20.<br />\r\n			Trasferimento in albergo e sistemazione.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 5</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">Samarcanda</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Samarcanda:</em></strong> Mausoleo Gur-Emir (15c), Registan Ensemble (incluso Ulugbek (15c), Shir Dor (17c), Tillya –Kari Madrassah (17c), Moschea Bibi Khanum Visita al bazar di Samarcanda.<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero.<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Samarcanda:</em></strong> Necropoli di Shah-i-Zinda (14-15c), \"Stelle sopra Samarcanda\": visita all\'osservatorio di Ulugbek (15c), Riserva archeologica statale \"Rovine di Afrosiab\" (6 aC-13 dC)<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera.</strong></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 6</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">Samarkanda - Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td valign=\"top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			Tempo libero.<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero.</strong><br />\r\n			Trasferimento alla stazione ferroviaria, treno per Tashkent alle 17.30, arrive alle 19.44. Trasferimento in albergo e sistemazione.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 7</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td valign=\"top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			Trasferimento all\'aeroporto di Tashkent, volo di ritorno.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong><em>Fine dei nostril servizi…</em></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '2', 'App\Models\Tour');
INSERT INTO translations (locale, column_name, value, translatable_id, translatable_type) VALUES ('en', 'route_lines', '<table class=\"table tour-table-rounded\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th style=\"width:8%;\">Days</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:14%;\">Waypoint</th>\r\n			<th>Subjects of itinerary</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 1<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Arrival to Tashkent. Transfer and accommodation at hotel.<br />\r\n			Free at leisure time.<br />\r\n			<strong>Lunch on self arrangement.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Tashkent: </em></strong>Visit to Tashkent Metro, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~750]]\" title=\"Catholic Polish Church\">Catholic Polish Church</a>, German Kirsch. <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~744]]\" title=\"Kukeldash Madrassah\">Kukeldash Madrassah</a>, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~709]]\" title=\"Kaffal Shashi Mausoleum\">Kaffal Shashi Mausoleum</a>, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~711]]\" title=\"Barak Khan Madrassah\">Barak Khan Madrassah</a>, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~686]]\" title=\"Mosque on Khasty Imam Street\">Mosque on Khasty Imam Street</a>, Visit to <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~710]]\" title=\"Chor-Su\">Chor-Su</a> – oriental market (handicraft bazaar)<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 2<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent -<br />\r\n			Kokand - Marguilan</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast.</strong><br />\r\n			Transfer to Train Station, train to Kokand at 08.00 arrival at 12.00.<br />\r\n			<strong>Lunch on self arrangement.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Sightseeing tour of Kokand</em></strong>: <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"uzbekistan-cities/kokand/sightseeing-in-kokand/khudayar-khan-fortress.html\" title=\"Khudayar Khan’s Palace\">Khudayar Khan’s Palace</a> (18-19 c); Juma Mosque (19 c); Norbutabei Madrassah (18 c); Royal cemetery.<br />\r\n			Transfer to Margilan and accommodation at traditional guest house Adras.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 3<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Margilan -<br />\r\n			Rishtan -<br />\r\n			Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast.</strong><br />\r\n			Visit Margilan with it\'s famous silk making factory \"Yodgorlik\". Continue driving to Rishtan, visit famous Rishtan ceramic workshop.<br />\r\n			<strong>Lunch on self arrangement </strong><br />\r\n			&nbsp;Afternoon at 15.00 drive to Margilan train station, train for Tashkent at 16.00. Arrival to Tashkent at 20.45, transfer to hotel and accommodation.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 4<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent - Samarkand</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast. </strong><br />\r\n			Transfer to Train Station, train to Samarkand at 08.00. Arrival to Samarkand at 10.10, transfer to hotel and accommodation.<br />\r\n			<strong>Lunch on self arrangement.</strong><br />\r\n			Free at leisure time.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 5<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Samarkand</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Samarkand:</em></strong> <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"uzbekistan-cities/samarkand/sightseeing-in-samarkand/gur-emir-mausoleum.html\" title=\"Gur-Emir Mausoleum\">Gur-Emir Mausoleum</a> (15c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"uzbekistan-cities/samarkand/sightseeing-in-samarkand/the-registan-square-most-popular-sight-of-interest-in-samarkand.html\" title=\"Registan Ensemble\">Registan Ensemble</a> (including <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"uzbekistan-cities/samarkand/sightseeing-in-samarkand/ulugbek-observatory.html\" title=\"Ulugbek\">Ulugbek</a> (15c), Shir Dor (17c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"uzbekistan-cities/samarkand/sightseeing-in-samarkand/tilla-kori-madrasah.html\" title=\"Tillya –Kari Madrassahs\">Tillya –Kari Madrassahs</a> (17c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"uzbekistan-cities/samarkand/sightseeing-in-samarkand/bibi-khanum-madrasah.html\" title=\"Bibi Khanum Mosque\">Bibi Khanum Mosque</a>. Visit to Samarkand bazaar.<br />\r\n			<strong>Lunch on self arrangement.<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Samarkand:</em></strong> <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"uzbekistan-cities/samarkand/sightseeing-in-samarkand/shakhi-zinda-necropolis.html\" title=\"Shah-i-Zinda necropolis\">S</a></strong><a class=\"in_text\" href=\"uzbekistan-cities/samarkand/sightseeing-in-samarkand/shakhi-zinda-necropolis.html\" title=\"Shah-i-Zinda necropolis\">hah-i-Zinda necropolis</a> (14-15c),\"Stars above Samarkand\": tour to <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"uzbekistan-cities/samarkand/sightseeing-in-samarkand/ulugbek-observatory.html\" title=\"Ulugbek observatory\">Ulugbek observatory</a> (15c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"uzbekistan-cities/samarkand/sightseeing-in-samarkand/afrasiab-the-settlement-of-the-ancient-orient.html\" title=\"“Ruins of Afrosiab” State archaeological reserve\">“Ruins of Afrosiab” State archaeological reserve</a> (6 BC-13 AD)<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 6<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Samarkand - Bukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast. </strong><br />\r\n			Transfer to Train Station, train to Bukhara at 09.45. Arrival to Bukhara at 11.47, transfer to hotel and accommodation.<br />\r\n			<strong>Lunch on self arrangement.</strong><br />\r\n			Free at leisure time.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 7<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Bukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Bukhara:</em></strong> <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~769]]\" title=\"Poi-Kalyan Ensemble including Minaret\">Poi-Kalyan Ensemble including Minaret</a> (12c) Mosque (15c), functioning <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~766]]\" title=\"Madrassah Miri-Arab\">Madrassah Miri-Arab</a> (16 c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~779]]\" title=\"Emir-Alim-Khan Madrassah\">Emir-Alim-Khan Madrassah</a> (14c), Taqi (trading domes), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~744]]\" title=\"Kukeldash Madrassah\">Kukeldash Madrassah</a> (16c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~763]]\" title=\"Nadir Divanbegi\">Nadir Divanbegi</a> (17c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~803]]\" title=\"Magok-i-Attari Mosque\">Magok-i-Attari Mosque</a>(16c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~703]]\" title=\"Lyab-i-Hauz\">Lyab-i-Hauz</a> (17c).<br />\r\n			<strong>Lunch on self arrangement. </strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Bukhara</em></strong>: Visit to Registan, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~767]]\" title=\"Ark Fortress\">Ark Fortress</a> (16 c) and <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~692]]\" title=\"Bolo-Hauz complex\">Bolo-Hauz complex</a> (18 c). <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~822]]\" title=\"Ulugbeg\">Ulugbeg</a> (15c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~801]]\" title=\"Abdul Aziz\">Abdul Aziz</a> (17c) <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~786]]\" title=\"Ismael Samani mausoleum\">Ismael Samani mausoleum</a> (9-10c)-vault of Bukhara rulers dynasty, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~804]]\" title=\"Chashma-Ayub Mausoleums\">Chashma-Ayub Mausoleums</a> (14 c)<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 8<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Bukhara – Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast. </strong><br />\r\n			Free at leisure time.<br />\r\n			<strong>Lunch on self arrangement. </strong><br />\r\n			Transfer to Train Station, train to Tashkent at 15.52. Arrival to Tashkent at 19.40, transfer to hotel and accommodation.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 9<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast. </strong><br />\r\n			Transfer to Tashkent Airport, flight back home.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong><em>End of our service…</em></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '3', 'App\Models\Tour');
INSERT INTO translations (locale, column_name, value, translatable_id, translatable_type) VALUES ('es', 'route_lines', '<table class=\"table tour-table-rounded\">\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th style=\"width:10%;\">DÍAS</td>\r\n			<th style=\"width:14%;\">TRAYECTO</td>\r\n			<th>ITINERARIO</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">DÍA 1<br />\r\n			SAT</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Tashkent</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Llegada a Tashkent. Traslado y alojamiento en hotel.<br />\r\n			Tiempo libre.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Comida.(Libre)</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visitas en Tashkent: </em></strong>Metro de Tashkent, Iglesia Católica. Plaza Jasty Imam: Mausoleo Kaffal Shashi, Madrazas Barakjan, Muyi Muborak; Mesquitas Tilla Sheikh, Jasty Imom; Bazar Chor-Su – Mercado oriental (de especies, frutas secas, quesos etc.)<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena (Libre)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">DÍA 2<br />\r\n			SUN</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Tashkent - Samarkand</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Desayuno.</strong><br />\r\n			Traslado a la Estación de Tren, tomar el tren a Samarkanda a las 07.00 y llegada a las 10.40, traslao y alojamiento en hotel.<br />\r\n			Tiempolibre</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Comida.(Libre)</strong><br />\r\n			Tiempo libre.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena. (Libre)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">DÍA 3<br />\r\n			MON</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Samarkand</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Desayuno.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visitas en Samarkanda:</em></strong> Mausoleo Gur-Emir (XV), El complejo de la Plaza de Registan: Madrazas Ulugbek (XV), Sher Dor (XVII), Tillya –Kari (XVII); Mezquita Bibi Khanum ( dedicado a la esposa de Tamerlán), Mercado Siyab (Mercado de especies, frutas secas, dulces, panes y etc.)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Comida</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visitas en Samarkanda:</em></strong> Necrópolis Shah-i-Zinda (XIV-XV), Las ruinas del observatorio de Ulugbek (XV), Museo Afrasiab:\"Ruinas de Afrosiab\" el campo arqueológico (s VII AC-s.XIII)<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena (Libre)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">DÍA 4<br />\r\n			TUE</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Samarkand - Bukhara</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Desayuno.</strong><br />\r\n			Traslado a la Estación de Tren para tomar el tren a Bujara a las 11.10</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Comida.(Libre)</strong><br />\r\n			Llegada a Bujara a las 14.30, traslado y alojamiento en hotel<br />\r\n			Tiempo libre.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena. (Libre)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">DÍA 5<br />\r\n			WED</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Bukhara - Urgench</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Desayuno.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visitas en Bukhara:</em></strong> Mausoleo de Ismael Samani (siglos IX-X), Mausoleo Chashma-Ayub (s XVII), Mezquita Bolo-Hauz (s.XVIII), Ciudadela Ark: Residencia de los Emires de Bukhara; Minarete Kalyan (siglo XII), Mezquita Poi-Kalyan (siglo XV), Madrassah Miri-Arab (s.XVI) en función, Emir Alim-Khan Madrassah (XX), Madrazas Ulug Beg (XV), Abdulazizxon (XVII)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Comida. (Libre)</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visitas en Bukhara</em></strong>: Mercados medievales: Toqi Zargaron, Toqi Telpakfurushon, Toqi Sarafon; Mezquita Magok-i-Attari (s.XII-XVI), Complejo Lyabi Hauz: Madraza Kukaldosh (s XVI), Khonaqo-Nadir Divanbegi (s XVII), Madraza Nadir Divanbegi (s XVII), Minarete Chor-Minor<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena. (Libre) </strong><br />\r\n			Traslado a la Estación de Trenes, tomar el tren a Urgench a las 21.15.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">DÍA 6<br />\r\n			THU</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Urgench - Khiva</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Desayuno. </strong><br />\r\n			Llegada a Urgench a las 09.30, traslado y alojamiento en hotel.<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visitas en Khiva:</em></strong>Ciudadela Kunya-Ark, Madrazas Muhammad Amin-xan (XIX), Muhammad Rahim-xan (XIX), Shirgazi-xan (XVII), Muhammad Amin-inaka (XVII), Kutlug Murad-inaka (XIX). Alla-quli-xan(XIX), Kazi-Kalyan(XX), Islam Khodja (XX)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Comida.(Libre)</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visitas en Khiva</em></strong>: Minarete Kalta-Minor (XIX), Minarete de la Mezquita de Djuma(XVIII), Minarete Islam Khodja (XX), Palacio Tash Khavli (patio de piedras) y Harem (XVIII-XIX), Mausoleos Uch Avliya (XVI), Said Allauddin (XIV), Pahlovon- Mahmud (XIX), Mirador de la ciudad<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena. (Libre)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">DÍA 7<br />\r\n			FRI</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Khiva - Urgench</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Desayuno</strong><br />\r\n			Tiempolibre.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Comida.(Libre)</strong><br />\r\n			Traslado a la Estación de Tren de Urgench, para tomar el tren a Tashkent a las 15.45<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena.(Libre)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">DÍA 8<br />\r\n			SAT</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Tashkent</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Desayuno.</strong><br />\r\n			Llegada aTashkent a las 10.45. Traslado y alojamiento en hotel.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Traslado al aeropuerto de Tashkent, Vuelo al destino</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong><em>Fin de nuestros servicios…</em></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n</table>', '3', 'App\Models\Tour');
INSERT INTO translations (locale, column_name, value, translatable_id, translatable_type) VALUES ('fr', 'route_lines', '<table class=\"table tour-table-rounded\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th style=\"width:10%;\">JOURS</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:14%;\">TRAJET</th>\r\n			<th>ITINERAIRE</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 1<br />\r\n			VENDREDI</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tachkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Arrivée à Tachkent. Transfert et installation à l\'hôtel.<br />\r\n			Temps libre.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			<strong>Dîner</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 2<br />\r\n			SAMEDI</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tachkent - Samarcande</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Petit déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Transfert à la gare. Train pour Samarcande à 08.00. Arrivée à 10.10. Transfert et hébergement à l’hôtel.<br />\r\n			Temps libre.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Temps libre.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dîner</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 3<br />\r\n			DIMANCHE</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Samarcande</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Petit déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visite de Samarcande:</em></strong> mausolée Gour-Emir (15C), Registan Ensemble (y compris Oulougbek (15C), Shir Dor (de 17c), Tillia -Kari medersas (17c), la mosquée Bibi Khanoum, visite de bazar orientale ‘‘Siab’’.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Poursuite de la visite de Samarcande :</em></strong> Shah-i-Zinda (14-15c), \"Etoiles au-dessus Samarcande\" visite de l\'observatoire d’Oulougbek (15c), «Ruines d\'Afrasyab\" réserve archéologique d’état (6 BC-13 AD)<br />\r\n			<strong>Dîner</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 4<br />\r\n			LUNDI</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Samarcande - Boukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Petit déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Transfert à la gare. Train pour Boukhara a 12.30. Arrivée à 15.30. Transfert et hébergement à l’hôtel. Temps libre</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Temps libre.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dîner</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 5<br />\r\n			MARDI</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Boukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Petit déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visite de Boukhara:</em></strong> : Poi-Kalyan Ensemble notamment Minaret (12c) Mosquée (15c), Miri-Arab (16 c) la médersa fonctionnant, Emir-Alim-Khan médersa (14c), Taqi (Les dômes de commerce), Koukeldash médersa (16c), Nadir Divanbegi (17c), la Mosquée Magok-i-Attari (16c), Lyab-i-Hauz (17c).</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Suite de visite guidée de Boukhara</em></strong>: Visite de Registan, la forteresse Ark (16 c) et complexe Bolo-Hauz (18 c). Oulougbek (15c), Abdul Aziz (17c) IsmaelSamani mausolées (9-10c) - caveau de la dynastie dirigeantes de Boukhara, Chashma-Ayub Mausolées (14 c)<br />\r\n			<strong>Dîner</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 6<br />\r\n			MERCREDI</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Boukhara - Ourguentch</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Petit déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Temps libre.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Temps libre.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dîner</strong><br />\r\n			Transfert à la gare. Train de nuit pour Ourguentch à 21.10. Nuit en train.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 7<br />\r\n			JEUDI</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Ourguentch-</h4>\r\n\r\n			<h4>Khiva</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Petit déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Arrivéeà Ourguentch à 09.00, transfert à Khiva (30 km.) et hébergement à l’hôtel.<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visite de Khiva:</em></strong> la forteresse KoukhnaArk, y compris KurinishKhana (17c) ; Mohammed Amin Khan (19c) médersa, Islam Khodja Minaret ; Complexe Palvan-Kari, Abd Al Bobo complexe (18c), Rafanek médersa, Mohammed Khan Rakim (19 c), Amir-Tur médersa, le mausolée Bobo Sho-I-Kalandar.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner.</strong><br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Poursuite de la visite de Khiva</em></strong>: Mazary Sharif médersa, le puits Kheivak (10c), OuchAvlioli (\"trois saints\") Mausolée, Mosquée Jouma (de 18c), Koutlouq-Mourad Inaq (19c) médersas, Mausolée Mahmoud Pakhlavan, palace TashHaouli («cour de pierre \"), des medersas Alla-Kouli-Khan (18c) et ArabMokhammed Khan (18 c).<br />\r\n			<strong>Diner.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 8<br />\r\n			VENDREDI</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Khiva -</h4>\r\n\r\n			<h4>Ourguentch -</h4>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Tachkent</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Petit déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Transfert à l’aéroport d’Ourguentch, vol pour Tachkent à 10.10 par HY-1052. Arrivéeà 12.55. Transfert et hébergementà l’hôtel.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visite de Tachkent: </em></strong> Metro de Tachkent, Église catholique polonaise, Eglise allemande. Koukeldash médersa, le mausolée Shashi Kaffal, médersa Barak Khan, Mosquée à Khasty Imam place, visite de Chor-Su - marché oriental (artisanat bazar)<br />\r\n			<strong>Dîner</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 9<br />\r\n			SAMEDI</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tachkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Petit déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Temps libre.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Transfert à l\'aéroport. Envol.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong><em>Fin de nos services ...</em></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"3\" valign=\"top\">\r\n			<p><strong><em>Prix par personne en USD: </em></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '3', 'App\Models\Tour');
INSERT INTO translations (locale, column_name, value, translatable_id, translatable_type) VALUES ('it', 'route_lines', '<table class=\"table tour-table-rounded\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th style=\"width:8%;\">Giorni</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:14%;\">Tappe</th>\r\n			<th>Soggetti dell’itinerario</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 1<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Tempo libero. Arrivo a Tashkent. Trasferimento e sistemazione in albergo.<br />\r\n			Tempo libero.<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Tashkent: </em></strong>Visita alla metropolitana di Tashkent, Chiesa cattolica polacca, Kirsch tedesco. Kukeldash Madrassah, Mausoleo di Kaffal Shashi, Barak Khan Madrassah, Moschea in Khasty Imam Street, Visita a Chor-Su – mercato orientale (bazar dell\'artigianato)<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 2<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent -<br />\r\n			Kokand - Marguilan</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			Trasferimento alla stazione ferroviaria, treno per Kokand alle 08.00 arrivo alle 12.00.<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico di Kokand</em></strong>: Palazzo di Khudayar Khan (18-19 c); Moschea Juma (19 c); Norbutabei Madrassah (18 c); Cimitero reale.<br />\r\n			Trasferimento a Margilan e sistemazione presso la tradizionale pensione Adras.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 3<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Margilan -<br />\r\n			Rishtan -<br />\r\n			Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			Visita Margilan con la sua famosa fabbrica di seta \"Yodgorlik\". Continua a guidare verso Rishtan, visita il famoso laboratorio di ceramica di Rishtan.<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero </strong><br />\r\n			&nbsp;Pomeriggio alle 15.00 in auto fino alla stazione ferroviaria di Margilan, treno per Tashkent alle 16.00. Arrivo a Tashkent alle 20.45, trasferimento in albergo e sistemazione.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 4<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent - Samarcanda</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione. </strong><br />\r\n			TTrasferimento alla stazione ferroviaria, treno per Samarcanda alle 08.00. Arrivo a Samarcanda alle 10.10, trasferimento in hotel e sistemazione.<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero.</strong><br />\r\n			Tempo libero.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 5<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Samarcanda</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Samarcanda:</em></strong> Mausoleo Gur-Emir (15c), Registan Ensemble (incluso Ulugbek (15c), Shir Dor (17c), Tillya –Kari Madrassah (17c), Moschea Bibi Khanum Visita al bazar di Samarcanda.<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero.<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Samarcanda:</em></strong> Necropoli di Shah-i-Zinda (14-15c), \"Stelle sopra Samarcanda\": visita all\'osservatorio di Ulugbek (15c), Riserva archeologica statale \"Rovine di Afrosiab\" (6 aC-13 dC)<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 6<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Samarcanda - Bukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione. </strong><br />\r\n			Trasferimento alla stazione ferroviaria, treno per Bukhara alle 09:45. Arrivo a Bukhara alle 11.47, trasferimento in hotel e sistemazione.<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero.</strong><br />\r\n			Tempo libero.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 7<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Bukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Bukhara:</em></strong> Poi-Kalyan Ensemble che include Minareto (12c) Moschea (15c), Madrassah Miri-Arab funzionante (16c), Emir-Alim-Khan Madrassah (14c), Taqi (cupole commerciali), Kukeldash Madrassah (16c) , Nadir Divanbegi (17c), Moschea Magok-i-Attari (16c), Lyab-i-Hauz (17c).<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero. </strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Bukhara</em></strong>: Visita al Registan, alla Fortezza dell\'Arca (16 sec) e al complesso Bolo-Hauz (18 sec). Ulugbeg (15c), Abdul Aziz (17c) Mausoleo di Ismael Samani (9-10c)-volta della dinastia dei sovrani di Bukhara, Mausolei di Chashma-Ayub (14c)<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 8<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Bukhara – Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione. </strong><br />\r\n			Tempo libero.<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero. </strong><br />\r\n			TTrasferimento alla stazione ferroviaria, treno per Tashkent alle 15:52. Arrivo a Tashkent alle 19.40, trasferimento in albergo e sistemazione.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 9<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione. </strong><br />\r\n			Trasferimento all\'aeroporto di Tashkent, volo di ritorno.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong><em>Fine dei nostri servizi…</em></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '3', 'App\Models\Tour');
INSERT INTO translations (locale, column_name, value, translatable_id, translatable_type) VALUES ('en', 'route_lines', '<table class=\"table tour-table-rounded\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th style=\"width:8%;\">Days</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:14%;\">Waypoint</th>\r\n			<th>Subjects of itinerary</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 1<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent - Khiva</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Morning arrival to Tashkent via Istanbul / Moscow. Transfer and accommodation in hotel (early check-in from 03h00 morning is included). Rest after long flight.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast.</strong><br />\r\n			Free at leisure time.<br />\r\n			<strong>Lunch on self arrangement.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Tashkent: </em></strong></strong>Visit to Tashkent Metro, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~750]]\" title=\"Catholic Polish Church\">Catholic Polish Church</a>, German Kirsch. <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~744]]\" title=\"Kukeldash Madrassah\">Kukeldash Madrassah</a>, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~709]]\" title=\"Kaffal Shashi Mausoleum\">Kaffal Shashi Mausoleum</a>, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~711]]\" title=\"Barak Khan Madrassah\">Barak Khan Madrassah</a>, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~686]]\" title=\"Mosque on Khasty Imam Street\">Mosque on Khasty Imam Street</a>, Visit to <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~710]]\" title=\"Chor-Su\">Chor-Su</a> – oriental market (handicraft bazaar)<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement.</strong><br />\r\n			Transfer to Train Station, for train to Urgench at 20.27. Overnight in the train</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 2<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Khiva</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast on self arrangement</strong><br />\r\n			Arrival to Urgench at 11.02. Transfer to Khiva (30km) and accommodation at hotel.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>Lunch on self arrangement. </strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Khiva: </em></strong><a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~716]]\" title=\"Kunya-Ark fortress\">Kunya-Ark fortress</a>, including Kurinish Khana (17c); <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~830]]\" title=\"Mohammed-Amin-Khan\">Mohammed-Amin-Khan</a>(19c) Madrassah, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~761]]\" title=\"Islam Khodja Minaret\">Islam Khodja Minaret</a>; <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~2160]]\" title=\"Palvan-Kari complex\">Palvan-Kari complex</a>, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~827]]\" title=\"Abd Al Bobo complex\">Abd Al Bobo complex</a>(18c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~2165]]\" title=\"Rafanek Madrassah\">Rafanek Madrassah</a>, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~833]]\" title=\"Mohammed Rakim Khan\">Mohammed Rakim Khan</a> (19 c), Amir-Tur Madrassah, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~828]]\" title=\"Sho-I-Kalandar Bobo Mausoleum\">Sho-I-Kalandar Bobo Mausoleum</a>, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~831]]\" title=\"Mazary Sharif Madrassah\">Mazary Sharif Madrassah</a>, Kheivak well (10c), Uch Avlioli (\"three saints\") Mausoleum, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~821]]\" title=\"Juma Mosque\">Juma Mosque</a> (18c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~826]]\" title=\"Kutluq-Murad Inaq\">Kutluq-Murad Inaq</a> (19c) Madrassah, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~789]]\" title=\"Pakhlavan Mahmoud Mausoleum\">Pakhlavan Mahmoud Mausoleum</a>, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~772]]\" title=\"Tash Hauli (\">Tash Hauli (\"stone yard\") Palace</a>, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~784]]\" title=\"Alla-Kuli-Khan\">Alla-Kuli-Khan</a> (18c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~774]]\" title=\"Arab Mohammed Khan\">Arab Mohammed Khan</a>(18 c) Madrassahs.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 3<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Khiva -<br />\r\n			Bukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast. </strong><br />\r\n			Free at leisure time for self-discover.<br />\r\n			<strong>Lunch on self arrangement.</strong><br />\r\n			Transfer to Train Station at 14h00, for train to Bukhara at 15.50.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Arrival at 22h47, transfer and accommodation in hotel.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 4<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Bukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Bukhara:</em></strong> <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~769]]\" title=\"Poi-Kalyan Ensemble including Minaret\">Poi-Kalyan Ensemble including Minaret</a> (12c) Mosque (15c), functioning <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~766]]\" title=\"Madrassah Miri-Arab\">Madrassah Miri-Arab</a> (16 c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~779]]\" title=\"Emir-Alim-Khan Madrassah\">Emir-Alim-Khan Madrassah</a> (14c), Taqi (trading domes), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~744]]\" title=\"Kukeldash Madrassah\">Kukeldash Madrassah</a> (16c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~763]]\" title=\"Nadir Divanbegi\">Nadir Divanbegi</a> (17c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~803]]\" title=\"Magok-i-Attari Mosque\">Magok-i-Attari Mosque</a>(16c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~703]]\" title=\"Lyab-i-Hauz\">Lyab-i-Hauz</a> (17c).<br />\r\n			<strong>Lunch on self arrangement. </strong><br />\r\n			<strong><strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Bukhara</em></strong>: </strong>Visit to Registan, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~767]]\" title=\"Ark Fortress\">Ark Fortress</a> (16 c) and <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~692]]\" title=\"Bolo-Hauz complex\">Bolo-Hauz complex</a> (18 c). <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~822]]\" title=\"Ulugbeg\">Ulugbeg</a> (15c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~801]]\" title=\"Abdul Aziz\">Abdul Aziz</a> (17c) <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~786]]\" title=\"Ismael Samani mausoleum\">Ismael Samani mausoleum</a> (9-10c)-vault of Bukhara rulers dynasty, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~804]]\" title=\"Chashma-Ayub Mausoleums\">Chashma-Ayub Mausoleums</a> (14 c)<strong>.<br />\r\n			Dinner on self arrangement</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 5<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Bukhara — Samarkand</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td><br />\r\n			<strong>Breakfast.</strong><br />\r\n			Free at leisure time for self-discover.<br />\r\n			<strong>Lunch on self arrangement.</strong><br />\r\n			Afternoon at 14h00 transfer to train station for speed train to Samarkand at 15h50. Arrival at 17h20. Transfer and accommodation in hotel.<br />\r\n			<strong><strong><strong>Dinner on self arrangement.&nbsp; </strong></strong></strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 6<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Samarkand</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong><strong><strong><strong>Breakfast.<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Samarkand:</em></strong> </strong></strong></strong></strong><a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~776]]\" title=\"Gur-Emir Mausoleum\">Gur-Emir Mausoleum</a> (15c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~697]]\" title=\"Registan Ensemble\">Registan Ensemble</a> including <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~822]]\" title=\"Ulugbeg\">Ulugbeg</a> (15c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~765]]\" title=\"Shir Dor\">Shir Dor</a> (17c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~768]]\" title=\"Tillya–Kari Madrassahs\">Tillya–Kari Madrassahs</a> (17c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~775]]\" title=\"Bibi Khanum Mosque\">Bibi Khanum Mosque</a>. Visit to Samarkand bazaar.<br />\r\n			<strong>Lunch on self arrangement.<br />\r\n			<strong><strong><strong><strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Samarkand:</em></strong> </strong></strong></strong></strong><a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~764]]\" title=\"Shah-i-Zinda necropolis\">Shah-i-Zinda necropolis</a> (14-15c), \"Stars above Samarkand\": tour to <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~754]]\" title=\"Ulugbek observatory\">Ulugbek observatory</a> (15c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~595]]\" title=\"“Ruins of Afrosiab” State archaeological reserve\">“Ruins of Afrosiab” State archaeological reserve</a> (6 BC-13 AD)<br />\r\n			<strong><strong><strong><strong>Dinner on self arrangement. </strong></strong></strong></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 7<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Samarkand-Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast. </strong><br />\r\n			Free at leisure time.<br />\r\n			<strong>Lunch on self arrangement.</strong><br />\r\n			Transfer to Train Station, train to Tashkent at 17.30, arrival at 19.44. Transfer to hotel and accommodation.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 8<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast. </strong><br />\r\n			Transfer to Tashkent Airport, flight back home.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong><em>End of our service…</em></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '4', 'App\Models\Tour');
