ranzo libero </strong><br />\r\n			&nbsp;Pomeriggio alle 15.00 in auto fino alla stazione ferroviaria di Margilan, treno per Tashkent alle 16.00. Arrivo a Tashkent alle 20.45, trasferimento in albergo e sistemazione.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 4<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent - Samarcanda</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione. </strong><br />\r\n			TTrasferimento alla stazione ferroviaria, treno per Samarcanda alle 08.00. Arrivo a Samarcanda alle 10.10, trasferimento in hotel e sistemazione.<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero.</strong><br />\r\n			Tempo libero.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 5<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Samarcanda</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Samarcanda:</em></strong> Mausoleo Gur-Emir (15c), Registan Ensemble (incluso Ulugbek (15c), Shir Dor (17c), Tillya –Kari Madrassah (17c), Moschea Bibi Khanum Visita al bazar di Samarcanda.<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero.<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Samarcanda:</em></strong> Necropoli di Shah-i-Zinda (14-15c), \"Stelle sopra Samarcanda\": visita all\'osservatorio di Ulugbek (15c), Riserva archeologica statale \"Rovine di Afrosiab\" (6 aC-13 dC)<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 6<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Samarcanda - Bukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione. </strong><br />\r\n			Trasferimento alla stazione ferroviaria, treno per Bukhara alle 09:45. Arrivo a Bukhara alle 11.47, trasferimento in hotel e sistemazione.<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero.</strong><br />\r\n			Tempo libero.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 7<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Bukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Bukhara:</em></strong> Poi-Kalyan Ensemble che include Minareto (12c) Moschea (15c), Madrassah Miri-Arab funzionante (16c), Emir-Alim-Khan Madrassah (14c), Taqi (cupole commerciali), Kukeldash Madrassah (16c) , Nadir Divanbegi (17c), Moschea Magok-i-Attari (16c), Lyab-i-Hauz (17c).<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero. </strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Bukhara</em></strong>: Visita al Registan, alla Fortezza dell\'Arca (16 sec) e al complesso Bolo-Hauz (18 sec). Ulugbeg (15c), Abdul Aziz (17c) Mausoleo di Ismael Samani (9-10c)-volta della dinastia dei sovrani di Bukhara, Mausolei di Chashma-Ayub (14c)<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 8<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Bukhara – Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione. </strong><br />\r\n			Tempo libero.<br />\r\n			<strong>Pranzo libero. </strong><br />\r\n			TTrasferimento alla stazione ferroviaria, treno per Tashkent alle 15:52. Arrivo a Tashkent alle 19.40, trasferimento in albergo e sistemazione.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 9<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione. </strong><br />\r\n			Trasferimento all\'aeroporto di Tashkent, volo di ritorno.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong><em>Fine dei nostri servizi…</em></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '4', 'App\Models\Tour');
INSERT INTO translations (locale, column_name, value, translatable_id, translatable_type) VALUES ('de', 'route_lines', '<table class=\"table tour-table-rounded\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th style=\"width:10%;\">TAGE</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:14%;\">REISEROUTE</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:8%;\">ZEIT</th>\r\n			<th>THEMEN DER REISEROUTE</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">1.TAG<br />\r\n			Sa.</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Taschkent</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Morgen</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Ankunft in Taschkent. Beförderung und Unterbringung im Hotel.<br />\r\n			Zeit zur freien Verfügung.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>NachmitTAG</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Selbstgestaltetes Mittagessen</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Stadtrundfahrt in Taschkent: </em></strong>Besuch der Taschkent U-Bahn, der Katholische Kirche, der deutsche Kirche, Kukeldash Medrese, Kaffal Shashi Mausoleum, Barak Khan Medrese, Moschee auf der Chast Imam Straβe, Besuch des orientalischen Tschor-Su Markt (Handwerk Basar)<br />\r\n			<strong>Selbstgestaltetes Abendessen</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">2.TAG<br />\r\n			So.</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Taschkent - Samarkand</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Morgen</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Frühstuck</strong><br />\r\n			Transfer zum Bahnhof, Zug nach Samarkand um 07.00, Ankunft um 10.40 und Unterbringung im Hotel.<br />\r\n			Zeit zur freien Verfügung.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>NachmitTAG</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Selbstgestaltetes Mittagessen</strong><br />\r\n			Zeit zur freien Verfügung.<br />\r\n			<strong>Selbstgestaltetes Abendessen</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">3. TAG<br />\r\n			Mo.</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Samarkand</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Morgen</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Frühstuck</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Stadtrundfahrt in Samarkand:</em></strong> Gur-Emir Mausoleum (15Jh), Registan Ensemble (einschlieβlich Ulugbek (15Jh), Shir Dor (17Jh), Tillya –Kari Medressen (17Jh), Bibi Khanum Moschee. Besuch zum Basar in Samarkand.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>NachmitTAG</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Selbstgestaltetes Mittagessen</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Stadtrundfahrt in Samarkand:</em></strong> Shah-i-Zinda Friedhof (14-15Jh), \"Sterne über Samarkand\": Tour zur Ulugbek Sternwarte (15Jh), \"Ruinen von Afrosiab\" die Staatliche archäologische Reserve (6 v.Chr.-13 n.Chr.)<br />\r\n			<strong>Selbstgestaltetes Abendessen </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">4. TAG<br />\r\n			Di.</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Samarkand - Buchara</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Morgen</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Frühstuck</strong><br />\r\n			Transfer zum Bahnhof, Zug nach Buchara um 11.10.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>NachmitTAG</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Selbstgestaltetes Mittagessen</strong><br />\r\n			Ankunft in Buchara um 14.30, Beförderung und Unterbringung im Hotel.<br />\r\n			Zeit zur freien Verfügung.<br />\r\n			<strong>Selbstgestaltetes Abendessen</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">5. TAG<br />\r\n			Mi.</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3><em>Buchara - Urgench </em></h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Morgen</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Frühstuck</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Stadtrundfahrt in Bukhara:</em></strong> Das Poi-Kalon Ensemble einschlieβlich das Minarett (12Jh), die Moschee (15Jh), arbeitende Medresse Miri-Arab (16 Jh), die Emir-Alim-Khan Meddresse (14Jh), die Taqi (Hadelkuppeln), die Kukeldash Medresse (16Jh), die Nadir Divanbegi (17Jh), Magok-i-Attari Moschee(16Jh), Lyab-i-Hauz (17Jh).</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>NachmitTAG</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Selbstgestaltetes Mittagessen</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Stadtrundfahrt in Buchara</em></strong>: Besuch in Registan, der Arche Festung (16 Jh.) und des Bolo-Chaus Komplex (18 Jh), Ulug Beg (15Jh), Abdul Aziz (17Jh), Ismael Samani Mausoleum (9-10Jh) – Die Gruft der Buchara Herrscher-Dynastie, &nbsp;Tschaschma-Ajub Mausoleums (14 Jh)<br />\r\n			<strong>Selbstgestaltetes Abendessen</strong><br />\r\n			Transfer zum Bahnhof, Zug nach Urgentsch um 21.15.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">6.TAG<br />\r\n			Do.</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Urgentsch – Chiwa</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Morgen</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Frühstuck</strong><br />\r\n			Ankunft in Urgentsch um 09.30, Transfer/Beförderung nach Chiwa und Unterbringung im Hotel.<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Stadtrundfahrt in Chiwa:</em></strong> Die Kunya-Ark Festung, einschlieβlich Kurinisch Chana (17Jh); die Mohammed-Amin-Khan(19Jh) Medresse, das Islam Khoja Minarett; der Palvan-Kari Komplex, der Abd Al Bobo Komplex(18Jh), die Rafanek Medresse, die Mohammed Rakim Chan&nbsp; (19Jh), Amir-Tur Medressen, das Scho-I-Kalandar Bobo Mausoleum.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>NachmitTAG</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Selbstgestaltetes Mittagessen</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Stadtrundfahrt in Chiwa</em></strong>: Die Masary Scharif Medresse, Der Kheivak Brunnen (10Jh), das Utsch Avlioli (\"Drei Heiligen\") Mausoleum, die Dschuma Moschee (18Jh), die Kutluq-Murad Inaq (19Jh) Medresse, das Pachlavan Mahmoud Mausoleum, der Tash Hauli (\"Steinhof\") Palast, die Alla-Kuli-Khan (18Jh), Arab Mohammed Khan(18Jh) Medressen.<br />\r\n			<strong>Selbstgestaltetes Abendessen</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">7.TAG<br />\r\n			Fr.</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Chiwa - Urgentsch</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Morgen</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Frühstuck</strong><br />\r\n			Zeit zur freien Verfügung.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>NachmitTAG</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Selbstgestaltetes Mittagessen</strong><br />\r\n			Beförderung nach Urgentsch Bahnhof, Zug nach Taschkent um 15.45.<br />\r\n			<strong>Selbstgestaltetes Abendessen</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">8.TAG<br />\r\n			Sa.</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Taschkent</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Morgen</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Frühstuck</strong><br />\r\n			Ankunft in Taschkent um 10.45. Beförderung und Unterbringung im Hotel.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>NachmitTAG</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Beförderung zum Taschkent Flughafen, Rückflug nach Hause.<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Ende unserer Leistung …</em></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '4', 'App\Models\Tour');
INSERT INTO translations (locale, column_name, value, translatable_id, translatable_type) VALUES ('es', 'route_lines', '<table class=\"table tour-table-rounded\">\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th style=\"width:10%;\">DÍAS</td>\r\n			<th style=\"width:14%;\">TRAYECTO</td>\r\n			<th>ITINERARIO</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">DÍA 1<br />\r\n			SAT</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Tashkent</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Llegada a Tashkent. Traslado y alojamiento en hotel.<br />\r\n			Tiempo libre.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Comida.(Libre)</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visitas en Tashkent: </em></strong>Metro de Tashkent, Iglesia Católica. Plaza Jasty Imam: Mausoleo Kaffal Shashi, Madrazas Barakjan, Muyi Muborak; Mesquitas Tilla Sheikh, Jasty Imom; Bazar Chor-Su – Mercado oriental (de especies, frutas secas, quesos etc.)<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena (Libre)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">DÍA 2<br />\r\n			SUN</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Tashkent - Samarkand</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Desayuno.</strong><br />\r\n			Traslado a la Estación de Tren, tomar el tren a Samarkanda a las 07.00 y llegada a las 10.40, traslao y alojamiento en hotel.<br />\r\n			Tiempolibre</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Comida.(Libre)</strong><br />\r\n			Tiempo libre.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena. (Libre)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">DÍA 3<br />\r\n			MON</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Samarkand</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Desayuno.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visitas en Samarkanda:</em></strong> Mausoleo Gur-Emir (XV), El complejo de la Plaza de Registan: Madrazas Ulugbek (XV), Sher Dor (XVII), Tillya –Kari (XVII); Mezquita Bibi Khanum ( dedicado a la esposa de Tamerlán), Mercado Siyab (Mercado de especies, frutas secas, dulces, panes y etc.)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Comida</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visitas en Samarkanda:</em></strong> Necrópolis Shah-i-Zinda (XIV-XV), Las ruinas del observatorio de Ulugbek (XV), Museo Afrasiab:\"Ruinas de Afrosiab\" el campo arqueológico (s VII AC-s.XIII)<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena (Libre)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">DÍA 4<br />\r\n			TUE</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Samarkand - Bukhara</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Desayuno.</strong><br />\r\n			Traslado a la Estación de Tren para tomar el tren a Bujara a las 11.10</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Comida.(Libre)</strong><br />\r\n			Llegada a Bujara a las 14.30, traslado y alojamiento en hotel<br />\r\n			Tiempo libre.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena. (Libre)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">DÍA 5<br />\r\n			WED</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Bukhara - Urgench</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Desayuno.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visitas en Bukhara:</em></strong> Mausoleo de Ismael Samani (siglos IX-X), Mausoleo Chashma-Ayub (s XVII), Mezquita Bolo-Hauz (s.XVIII), Ciudadela Ark: Residencia de los Emires de Bukhara; Minarete Kalyan (siglo XII), Mezquita Poi-Kalyan (siglo XV), Madrassah Miri-Arab (s.XVI) en función, Emir Alim-Khan Madrassah (XX), Madrazas Ulug Beg (XV), Abdulazizxon (XVII)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Comida. (Libre)</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visitas en Bukhara</em></strong>: Mercados medievales: Toqi Zargaron, Toqi Telpakfurushon, Toqi Sarafon; Mezquita Magok-i-Attari (s.XII-XVI), Complejo Lyabi Hauz: Madraza Kukaldosh (s XVI), Khonaqo-Nadir Divanbegi (s XVII), Madraza Nadir Divanbegi (s XVII), Minarete Chor-Minor<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena. (Libre) </strong><br />\r\n			Traslado a la Estación de Trenes, tomar el tren a Urgench a las 21.15.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">DÍA 6<br />\r\n			THU</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Urgench - Khiva</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Desayuno. </strong><br />\r\n			Llegada a Urgench a las 09.30, traslado y alojamiento en hotel.<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visitas en Khiva:</em></strong>Ciudadela Kunya-Ark, Madrazas Muhammad Amin-xan (XIX), Muhammad Rahim-xan (XIX), Shirgazi-xan (XVII), Muhammad Amin-inaka (XVII), Kutlug Murad-inaka (XIX). Alla-quli-xan(XIX), Kazi-Kalyan(XX), Islam Khodja (XX)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Comida.(Libre)</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visitas en Khiva</em></strong>: Minarete Kalta-Minor (XIX), Minarete de la Mezquita de Djuma(XVIII), Minarete Islam Khodja (XX), Palacio Tash Khavli (patio de piedras) y Harem (XVIII-XIX), Mausoleos Uch Avliya (XVI), Said Allauddin (XIV), Pahlovon- Mahmud (XIX), Mirador de la ciudad<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena. (Libre)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">DÍA 7<br />\r\n			FRI</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Khiva - Urgench</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Desayuno</strong><br />\r\n			Tiempolibre.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Comida.(Libre)</strong><br />\r\n			Traslado a la Estación de Tren de Urgench, para tomar el tren a Tashkent a las 15.45<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena.(Libre)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">DÍA 8<br />\r\n			SAT</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h3>Tashkent</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Desayuno.</strong><br />\r\n			Llegada aTashkent a las 10.45. Traslado y alojamiento en hotel.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Traslado al aeropuerto de Tashkent, Vuelo al destino</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong><em>Fin de nuestros servicios…</em></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n</table>', '4', 'App\Models\Tour');
INSERT INTO translations (locale, column_name, value, translatable_id, translatable_type) VALUES ('fr', 'route_lines', '<table class=\"table tour-table-rounded\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th style=\"width:10%;\">JOURS</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:14%;\">TRAJET</th>\r\n			<th>ITINERAIRE</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 1<br />\r\n			VENDREDI</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tachkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Arrivée à Tachkent. Transfert et installation à l\'hôtel.<br />\r\n			Temps libre.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			<strong>Dîner</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 2<br />\r\n			SAMEDI</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tachkent - Samarcande</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Petit déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Transfert à la gare. Train pour Samarcande à 08.00. Arrivée à 10.10. Transfert et hébergement à l’hôtel.<br />\r\n			Temps libre.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Temps libre.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dîner</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 3<br />\r\n			DIMANCHE</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Samarcande</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Petit déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visite de Samarcande:</em></strong> mausolée Gour-Emir (15C), Registan Ensemble (y compris Oulougbek (15C), Shir Dor (de 17c), Tillia -Kari medersas (17c), la mosquée Bibi Khanoum, visite de bazar orientale ‘‘Siab’’.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Poursuite de la visite de Samarcande :</em></strong> Shah-i-Zinda (14-15c), \"Etoiles au-dessus Samarcande\" visite de l\'observatoire d’Oulougbek (15c), «Ruines d\'Afrasyab\" réserve archéologique d’état (6 BC-13 AD)<br />\r\n			<strong>Dîner</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 4<br />\r\n			LUNDI</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Samarcande - Boukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Petit déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Transfert à la gare. Train pour Boukhara a 12.30. Arrivée à 15.30. Transfert et hébergement à l’hôtel. Temps libre</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Temps libre.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dîner</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 5<br />\r\n			MARDI</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Boukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Petit déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visite de Boukhara:</em></strong> : Poi-Kalyan Ensemble notamment Minaret (12c) Mosquée (15c), Miri-Arab (16 c) la médersa fonctionnant, Emir-Alim-Khan médersa (14c), Taqi (Les dômes de commerce), Koukeldash médersa (16c), Nadir Divanbegi (17c), la Mosquée Magok-i-Attari (16c), Lyab-i-Hauz (17c).</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Suite de visite guidée de Boukhara</em></strong>: Visite de Registan, la forteresse Ark (16 c) et complexe Bolo-Hauz (18 c). Oulougbek (15c), Abdul Aziz (17c) IsmaelSamani mausolées (9-10c) - caveau de la dynastie dirigeantes de Boukhara, Chashma-Ayub Mausolées (14 c)<br />\r\n			<strong>Dîner</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 6<br />\r\n			MERCREDI</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Boukhara - Ourguentch</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Petit déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Temps libre.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Temps libre.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dîner</strong><br />\r\n			Transfert à la gare. Train de nuit pour Ourguentch à 21.10. Nuit en train.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 7<br />\r\n			JEUDI</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Ourguentch-</h4>\r\n\r\n			<h4>Khiva</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Petit déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Arrivéeà Ourguentch à 09.00, transfert à Khiva (30 km.) et hébergement à l’hôtel.<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visite de Khiva:</em></strong> la forteresse KoukhnaArk, y compris KurinishKhana (17c) ; Mohammed Amin Khan (19c) médersa, Islam Khodja Minaret ; Complexe Palvan-Kari, Abd Al Bobo complexe (18c), Rafanek médersa, Mohammed Khan Rakim (19 c), Amir-Tur médersa, le mausolée Bobo Sho-I-Kalandar.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner.</strong><br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Poursuite de la visite de Khiva</em></strong>: Mazary Sharif médersa, le puits Kheivak (10c), OuchAvlioli (\"trois saints\") Mausolée, Mosquée Jouma (de 18c), Koutlouq-Mourad Inaq (19c) médersas, Mausolée Mahmoud Pakhlavan, palace TashHaouli («cour de pierre \"), des medersas Alla-Kouli-Khan (18c) et ArabMokhammed Khan (18 c).<br />\r\n			<strong>Diner.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 8<br />\r\n			VENDREDI</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Khiva -</h4>\r\n\r\n			<h4>Ourguentch -</h4>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Tachkent</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Petit déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Transfert à l’aéroport d’Ourguentch, vol pour Tachkent à 10.10 par HY-1052. Arrivéeà 12.55. Transfert et hébergementà l’hôtel.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Visite de Tachkent: </em></strong> Metro de Tachkent, Église catholique polonaise, Eglise allemande. Koukeldash médersa, le mausolée Shashi Kaffal, médersa Barak Khan, Mosquée à Khasty Imam place, visite de Chor-Su - marché oriental (artisanat bazar)<br />\r\n			<strong>Dîner</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>JOUR 9<br />\r\n			SAMEDI</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tachkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Petit déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Temps libre.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Déjeuner</strong><br />\r\n			Transfert à l\'aéroport. Envol.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong><em>Fin de nos services ...</em></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"3\" valign=\"top\">\r\n			<p><strong><em>Prix par personne en USD: </em></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '4', 'App\Models\Tour');
INSERT INTO translations (locale, column_name, value, translatable_id, translatable_type) VALUES ('it', 'route_lines', '<table class=\"table tour-table-rounded\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th style=\"width:8%;\">Giorni</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:14%;\">Tappe</th>\r\n			<th>Soggetti dell’itinerario</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 1<br />\r\n			SAB</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Arrivo in mattinata a Tashkent via Istanbul/Mosca. Trasferimento e sistemazione in hotel. Il check-in anticipato dalle 18:00 è incluso.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Tashkent</em></strong>: Kukeldash Madrassah, Kaffal Shashi Mausoleum, Barak Khan Madrassah, Corano di Osman VII sec., Moschea in Khasty Imam Street, Visita a Chor-Su – mercato orientale (bazar dell\'artigianato).</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pranzo libero. </strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Tashkent</em></strong>: Visita alla metropolitana di Tashkent, Piazza Mustakillik (Piazza dell\'Indipendenza), Piazza Amir Temur, Monumento ad Alisher Navoi.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 2<br />\r\n			DOM</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent - Samarcanda</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Trasferimento alla stazione ferroviaria per il treno veloce Afrosiyob per Samarcanda alle 08.00. Arrivo alle 10.10.<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Samarcanda:</em></strong> Mausoleo Gur-Emir (15c), Registan Ensemble (incluso Ulugbek (15c), Shir Dor (17c), Tillya –Kari Madrassah (17c), Moschea Bibi Khanum Visita al bazar di Samarcanda.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pranzo libero </strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Samarcanda:</em></strong> necropoli di Shah-i-Zinda (14-15c),“Stelle sopra Samarcanda”: visita all\'osservatorio di Ulugbek (15c), Riserva archeologica statale “Rovine di Afrosiab” (6 aC-13 dC)<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 3<br />\r\n			LUN</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Samarcanda</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione. </strong><br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Giornata libera per la scoperta di se stessi.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pranzo libero.</strong><br />\r\n			Giornata libera per la scoperta di se stessi.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 4<br />\r\n			MAR</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Samarcanda - Bukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Trasferimento alla stazione ferroviaria per il treno veloce Afrosiyob per Bukhara alle 09:45. Arrivo alle 11.15, trasferimento e sistemazione in hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pranzo libero. </strong><br />\r\n			Giornata libera per la scoperta di se stessi.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 5<br />\r\n			MER</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Bukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Bukhara:</em></strong> Poi-Kalyan Ensemble che include Minareto (12c) Moschea (15c), Madrassah Miri-Arab funzionante (16c), Emir-Alim-Khan Madrassah (14c), Taqi (cupole commerciali), Kukeldash Madrassah (16c) , Nadir Divanbegi (17c), Moschea Magok-i-Attari (16c), Lyab-i-Hauz (17c).</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pranzo libero. </strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Bukhara</em></strong>: Visita al Registan, alla Fortezza dell\'Arca (16 sec) e al complesso Bolo-Hauz (18 sec). Ulugbeg (15c), Abdul Aziz (17c) Mausoleo di Ismael Samani (9-10c)-volta della dinastia dei sovrani di Bukhara, Mausolei di Chashma-Ayub (14c)<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 6<br />\r\n			GIO</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Bukhara –</h4>\r\n\r\n			<h4>Khiva</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Trasferimento a Khiva attraverso il deserto di Kyzyl-Kum. Lungo il percorso sosta presso la riva del fiume Amu-Daria (antico Oxus).</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pranzo libero.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Arrivo a Khiva nel tardo pomeriggio e sistemazione in albergo.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Cena libera</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 7<br />\r\n			VEN</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Khiva</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Khiva:</em></strong> fortezza Kunya-Ark, incluso Kurinish Khana (17c); Mohammed-Amin-Khan(19c) Madrasa, Minareto Islam Khodja; Complesso Palvan-Kari, complesso Abd Al Bobo (18c), Rafanek Madrassah, Mohammed Rakim Khan (19c), Amir-Tur Madrassah, Mausoleo Sho-I-Kalandar Bobo.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pranzo libero. </strong><br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Khiva</em></strong>: Mazary Sharif Madrassah, Kheivak well (10c), Uch Avlioli (\"tre santi\") Mausoleo, Moschea Juma (18c), Kutluq-Murad Inaq (19c) Madrassah, Mausoleo Pakhlavan Mahmoud, Tash Hauli (\"cortile di pietra ”) Palazzo, Alla-Kuli-Khan (18c), Madrasse arabe Mohammed Khan (18c).<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td align=\"center\" class=\"justifyleft\">GIORNO 8<br />\r\n			SAB</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Khiva –</h4>\r\n\r\n			<h4>Urgench –</h4>\r\n\r\n			<h4>Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione. </strong><br />\r\n			Trasferimento all\'aeroporto di Urgench, volo per Tashkent alle 09:35 con HY-1052, arrivo a Tashkent alle 12:20. Trasferimento in hotel e sistemazione.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pranzo libero. </strong><br />\r\n			Giornata libera per la scoperta di se stessi.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena di arrivederci in casa nazionale. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td align=\"center\" class=\"justifyleft\">GIORNO 9<br />\r\n			DOM</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione. </strong><br />\r\n			Trasferimento all\'aeroporto di Tashkent, volo di ritorno.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong><em>Fine del tuo meraviglioso viaggio in Uzbekistan…</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '5', 'App\Models\Tour');
INSERT INTO translations (locale, column_name, value, translatable_id, translatable_type) VALUES ('en', 'route_lines', '<table class=\"table tour-table-rounded\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th style=\"width:8%;\">Days</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:14%;\">Waypoint</th>\r\n			<th>Subjects of itinerary</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 1<br />\r\n			SAT</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Morning arrival in Tashkent via Istanbul / Moscow. Transfer and accommodation in hotel. Early check-in from 06h00 PM is included.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Tashkent</em></strong>: Kukeldash Madrassah, Kaffal Shashi Mausoleum, Barak Khan Madrassah, Osman’s Koran VII c., Mosque on Khasty Imam Street, Visit to Chor-Su – oriental market (handicraft bazaar).</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Lunch on self arrangement. </strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Tashkent</em></strong>: Visit to Tashkent Metro, Mustakillik Square (Independence Square), Amir Temur Square, Monument to Alisher Navoi.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 2<br />\r\n			SUN</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent - Samarkand</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Transfer to the railway station for the speed train Afrosiyob to Samarkand at 08.00. Arrival at 10.10.<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Samarkand:</em></strong> <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~776]]\" title=\"Gur-Emir Mausoleum\">Gur-Emir Mausoleum</a> (15c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~697]]\" title=\"Registan Ensemble\">Registan Ensemble</a> (including <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~754]]\" title=\"Ulugbek\">Ulugbek</a> (15c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~765]]\" title=\"Shir Dor\">Shir Dor</a> (17c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~768]]\" title=\"Tillya –Kari Madrassahs\">Tillya –Kari Madrassahs</a> (17c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~775]]\" title=\"Bibi Khanum Mosque\">Bibi Khanum Mosque</a>. Visit to Samarkand bazaar.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Lunch on self arrangement </strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Samarkand:</em></strong> <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~764]]\" title=\"Shah-i-Zinda necropolis\">Shah-i-Zinda necropolis</a> (14-15c),<br />\r\n			“Stars above Samarkand”: tour to <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~754]]\" title=\"Ulugbek observatory\">Ulugbek observatory</a> (15c), “<a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~595]]\" title=\"Ruins of Afrosiab\">Ruins of Afrosiab</a>” State archaeological reserve (6 BC-13 AD)<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 3<br />\r\n			MON</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Samarkand</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast. </strong><br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Free at leisure day for self-discover.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Lunch on self arrangement.</strong><br />\r\n			Free at leisure day for self-discover.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 4<br />\r\n			TUE</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Samarkand-Bukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Transfer to the railway station for the speed train Afrosiyob to Bukhara at 09.45. Arrival at 11.15, transfer and accommodation in hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Lunch on self arrangement. </strong><br />\r\n			Free at leisure time for self-discover.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 5<br />\r\n			WED</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Bukhara</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Bukhara:</em></strong> <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~769]]\" title=\"Poi-Kalyan Ensemble including Minaret\">Poi-Kalyan Ensemble including Minaret</a> (12c) Mosque (15c), functioning <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~766]]\" title=\"Madrassah Miri-Arab\">Madrassah Miri-Arab</a> (16 c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~779]]\" title=\"Emir-Alim-Khan Madrassah\">Emir-Alim-Khan Madrassah</a> (14c), Taqi (trading domes), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~744]]\" title=\"Kukeldash Madrassah\">Kukeldash Madrassah</a> (16c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~763]]\" title=\"Nadir Divanbegi\">Nadir Divanbegi</a> (17c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~803]]\" title=\"Magok-i-Attari Mosque\">Magok-i-Attari Mosque</a>(16c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~703]]\" title=\"Lyab-i-Hauz\">Lyab-i-Hauz</a> (17c).</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Lunch on self arrangement. </strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Bukhara</em></strong>: Visit to Registan, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~767]]\" title=\"Ark Fortress\">Ark Fortress</a> (16 c) and <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~692]]\" title=\"Bolo-Hauz complex\">Bolo-Hauz complex</a> (18 c). <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~822]]\" title=\"Ulugbeg\">Ulugbeg</a> (15c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~801]]\" title=\"Abdul Aziz\">Abdul Aziz</a> (17c) <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~786]]\" title=\"Ismael Samani mausoleum\">Ismael Samani mausoleum</a> (9-10c)-vault of Bukhara rulers dynasty, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~804]]\" title=\"Chashma-Ayub Mausoleums\">Chashma-Ayub Mausoleums</a> (14 c)<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 6<br />\r\n			THU</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Bukhara –</h4>\r\n\r\n			<h4>Khiva</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Transfer to Khiva through Kyzyl-Kum desert. En route stop by the bank of Amu-Daria river (ancient Oxus).</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Lunch on self arrangement.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Arrival to Khiva late afternoon and accommodation in hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Dinner on self arrangement</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DAY 7<br />\r\n			FRI</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Khiva</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Khiva:</em></strong> <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~716]]\" title=\"Kunya-Ark fortress\">Kunya-Ark fortress</a>, including Kurinish Khana (17c); <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~830]]\" title=\"Mohammed-Amin-Khan\">Mohammed-Amin-Khan</a>(19c) Madrassah, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~761]]\" title=\"Islam Khodja Minaret\">Islam Khodja Minaret</a>; <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~2160]]\" title=\"Palvan-Kari complex\">Palvan-Kari complex</a>, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~827]]\" title=\"Abd Al Bobo complex\">Abd Al Bobo complex</a>(18c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~2165]]\" title=\"Rafanek Madrassah\">Rafanek Madrassah</a>, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~833]]\" title=\"Mohammed Rakim Khan\">Mohammed Rakim Khan</a> (19 c), Amir-Tur Madrassah, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~828]]\" title=\"Sho-I-Kalandar Bobo Mausoleum\">Sho-I-Kalandar Bobo Mausoleum</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Lunch on self arrangement. </strong><br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Sightseeing tour in Khiva</em></strong>: <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~831]]\" title=\"Mazary Sharif Madrassah\">Mazary Sharif Madrassah</a>, Kheivak well (10c), Uch Avlioli (“three saints”) Mausoleum, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~821]]\" title=\"Juma Mosque\">Juma Mosque</a> (18c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~826]]\" title=\"Kutluq-Murad Inaq\">Kutluq-Murad Inaq</a> (19c) Madrassah, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~789]]\" title=\"Pakhlavan Mahmoud Mausoleum\">Pakhlavan Mahmoud Mausoleum</a>, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~772]]\" title=\"Tash Hauli (“stone yard”) Palace\">Tash Hauli (“stone yard”) Palace</a>, <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~784]]\" title=\"Alla-Kuli-Khan\">Alla-Kuli-Khan</a> (18c), <a class=\"in_text\" href=\"[[~774]]\" title=\"Arab Mohammed Khan\">Arab Mohammed Khan</a>(18 c) Madrassahs.<br />\r\n			<strong>Dinner on self arrangement</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td align=\"center\" class=\"justifyleft\">DAY 8<br />\r\n			SAT</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Khiva –</h4>\r\n\r\n			<h4>Urgench –</h4>\r\n\r\n			<h4>Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast. </strong><br />\r\n			Transfer to Urgench Airport, Flight to Tashkent at 09.35 by HY-1052, arrival to Tashkent at 12.20. Transfer to hotel and accommodation.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Lunch on self arrangement. </strong><br />\r\n			Free at leisure time for self-discover.<br />\r\n			<strong>Farewell Dinner in National house. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td align=\"center\" class=\"justifyleft\">DAY 9<br />\r\n			SUN</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h4>Tashkent</h4>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Breakfast. </strong><br />\r\n			Transfer to Tashkent Airport, flight back home.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong><em>End of your wonderful trip in Uzbekistan…</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '5', 'App\Models\Tour');
INSERT INTO translations (locale, column_name, value, translatable_id, translatable_type) VALUES ('it', 'route_lines', '<table class=\"table tour-table-rounded\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th style=\"width:8%;\">Giorni</th>\r\n			<th style=\"width:14%;\">Tappe</th>\r\n			<th>Soggetti dell’itinerario</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 1</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h3>Tashkent</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Arrivo a Tashkent. Trasferimento e sistemazione in hotel. Tempo libero.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pranzo.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Tashkent: </em></strong>Visita alla metropolitana di Tashkent, Chiesa cattolica polacca, Kirsch tedesco. Kukeldash Madrassah, Mausoleo di Kaffal Shashi, Barak Khan Madrassah, Moschea in Khasty Imam Street, Visita a Chor-Su – mercato orientale (bazar dell\'artigianato)<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 2</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h3>Tashkent - Urgench - Khiva</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			Trasferimento all\'aeroporto nazionale, volo per Urgench alle 07:25 Arrivo alle 08:55 trasferimento Khiva e sistemazione in hotel.<br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Khiva: </em></strong>fortezza Kunya-Ark, incluso Kurinish Khana (17c); Mohammed-Amin-Khan (19c) Madrasa, minareto Islam Khodja; Complesso Palvan-Kari, complesso Abd Al Bobo (18c), Rafanek Madrassah, Mohammed Rakim Khan (19c), Amir-Tur Madrassah, Mausoleo Sho-I-Kalandar Bobo.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pranzo.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Khiva</em></strong>:Mazary Sharif Madrassah, Kheivak well (10c), Uch Avlioli (\"tre santi\") Mausoleo, Moschea Juma (18c), Kutluq-Murad Inaq (19c) Madrassah, Mausoleo Pakhlavan Mahmoud, Tash Hauli (\"cortile di pietra ”) Palazzo, Alla-Kuli-Khan (18c), Madrasse arabe Mohammed Khan (18c).<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 3</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h3>Khiva - Bukhara</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			Trasferimento a Bukhara attraverso il deserto di Kyzyl-Kum e sosta sulla riva del fiume Amudarya.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pranzo al sacco</strong><br />\r\n			Arrivo e sistemazione, tempo libero.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 4</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h3>Bukhara</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione. </strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Bukhara:</em></strong> Ensemble Poi-Kalyan che include Minareto (12c) Moschea (15c), Madrassah Miri-Arab funzionante (16c), Emir-Alim-Khan Madrassah (14c), Taqi (cupole commerciali), Kukeldash Madrassah (16c) , Nadir Divanbegi (17c), Moschea Magok-i-Attari (16c), Lyab-i-Hauz (17c).</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pranzo libero.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Bukhara</em></strong>: Visita al Registan, alla Fortezza dell\'Arca (16 sec) e al complesso Bolo-Hauz (18 sec). Ulugbeg (15c), Abdul Aziz (17c) Mausoleo di Ismael Samani (9-10c)-volta della dinastia dei sovrani di Bukhara, Mausolei di Chashma-Ayub (14c)<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 5</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h3>Bukhara - Samarcanda</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico fuori Bukhara:</em> </strong>Visita alla residenza estiva dell\'emiro - \"Sitorai-Mokhi-Khosa\" (1911).<br />\r\n			Tempo libero</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pranzo. </strong><br />\r\n			Trasferimento a Samarcanda, arrivo e sistemazione.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 6</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h3>Samarcanda</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione. </strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>SGiro turistico a Samarcanda:</em></strong> Mausoleo Gur-Emir (15c), Registan Ensemble (incluso Ulugbek (15c), Shir Dor (17c), Tillya –Kari Madrassah (17c), Moschea Bibi Khanum Visita al bazar di Samarcanda.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pranzo.</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><em>Giro turistico a Samarcanda:</em></strong> necropoli di Shah-i-Zinda (14-15c), \"Stelle sopra Samarcanda\": visita all\'osservatorio di Ulugbek (15c), Riserva archeologica statale “Rovine di Afrosiab” (6 aC-13 dC)<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera. </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 7</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h3>Samarcanda - Tashkent</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione.</strong><br />\r\n			Tempo libero.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pranzo.</strong><br />\r\n			Trasferimento a Tashkent, arrive e sistemazione.<br />\r\n			<strong>Cena libera.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>GIORNO 8</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h3>Tashkent</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Colazione. </strong><br />\r\n			Trasferimento all’aeroporto.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong><em>Fine dei nostri servizi…</em></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '6', 'App\Models\Tour');
